WEBVTT

00:03.767 --> 00:05.968
♪

00:05.970 --> 00:07.186
(grunt, whooping)

00:07.188 --> 00:08.638
"D," "D," "D," "D!"

00:08.640 --> 00:10.323
"D" up, "D" up, "D" up!

00:10.325 --> 00:12.325
Two-point game, kid-- you better
make something happen quick.

00:12.327 --> 00:14.027
Can we just play
the game, Danny?

00:14.029 --> 00:15.278
Well, it looks
like we can play.

00:15.280 --> 00:16.779
I don't know if you can.
Too bad your jump shot

00:16.781 --> 00:18.531
isn't half as good as your trash talking.
Oh, my jump shot?

00:18.533 --> 00:20.816
Yeah.
My jump shot's about to make me 50 bucks,

00:20.818 --> 00:21.918
and it's gonna come
from your pocket.

00:21.920 --> 00:23.286
I'm not worried.
Yeah?

00:23.288 --> 00:24.671
You haven't made it from 20
since you were 20.

00:24.673 --> 00:26.289
Oh, really?
Well, maybe I'm due.

00:26.291 --> 00:27.757
DANNY:
What do you say?

00:27.759 --> 00:28.841
Right here.

00:28.843 --> 00:30.793
(grunting, whooping)

00:30.795 --> 00:32.579
(grunts)

00:32.581 --> 00:33.630
Come on!
Hold it.

00:33.632 --> 00:34.714
Lighten up, man!

00:34.716 --> 00:35.765
What the hell was that?

00:35.767 --> 00:37.183
What the hell was what?
That's like

00:37.185 --> 00:38.635
the fifth time
you body-slammed me today.

00:38.637 --> 00:41.020
Quit crying, old man.
DANNY: Hey, it was a hard foul.

00:41.022 --> 00:41.971
Take it easy.
You're high.

00:41.973 --> 00:43.172
That was all ball.
Hey, Jamie,

00:43.174 --> 00:44.274
talk to your teammate.

00:44.276 --> 00:45.308
He's been hacking my guys
all day.

00:45.310 --> 00:47.443
It was a foul.
Oh, come on.

00:47.445 --> 00:48.695
Only looked like a foul
'cause this

00:48.697 --> 00:50.063
fat slob couldn't
stay on his feet.

00:50.065 --> 00:51.064
What'd you just call me?

00:51.066 --> 00:52.482
I'm pretty sure
I called you a fat slob.

00:52.484 --> 00:53.950
Why, you prefer
lard-ass?

00:53.952 --> 00:55.451
Say it one more time.
Call me fat one more time.

00:55.453 --> 00:56.519
Why? What are you gonna do?

00:56.521 --> 00:57.870
Eat me?
That's it!

00:57.872 --> 00:59.405
(grunts)

00:59.407 --> 01:01.224
(groans)

01:01.226 --> 01:02.858
Hey!
Whoa! What's the matter with you?

01:02.860 --> 01:04.209
Whoa.

01:04.212 --> 01:05.578
(groans)

01:05.580 --> 01:07.029
JAMIE:
What's that? Hey!

01:07.031 --> 01:08.831
What are you doing?

01:08.833 --> 01:10.717
(panting)

01:10.719 --> 01:12.251
All right, all right.

01:12.253 --> 01:15.204
Is he all right?

01:22.546 --> 01:24.880
Commissioner, in the four years
since you've held this office,

01:24.882 --> 01:26.683
violent crime in
the city is down

01:26.685 --> 01:28.735
over 20% across
the board.

01:28.737 --> 01:31.404
Are these numbers we
should be happy with?

01:31.406 --> 01:33.740
Relative to when
I started, sure.

01:33.742 --> 01:35.024
Well, how low can you go?

01:35.026 --> 01:36.225
In a perfect world?

01:36.227 --> 01:37.343
Zero.

01:37.345 --> 01:39.412
But we don't live
in a perfect world.

01:39.414 --> 01:41.114
Well, what's your target?

01:41.116 --> 01:42.615
It's a moving target.

01:42.617 --> 01:44.701
I'd be a fool to set a number.

01:44.703 --> 01:46.869
We just take it
one day, one block,

01:46.871 --> 01:49.539
one successful intervention
at a time.

01:49.541 --> 01:52.542
Even if that means violating
civil liberties along the way?

01:52.544 --> 01:54.761
Like with stop and frisk?

01:56.030 --> 01:58.514
Stop, question and frisk.

01:58.516 --> 02:01.684
Our critics always leave out
that important second word.

02:01.686 --> 02:04.354
The fact is, most stops
don't end in searches,

02:04.356 --> 02:07.140
but when they do,
they're fruitful.

02:07.142 --> 02:10.759
Last year, we took back
more than 800 illegal guns.

02:10.762 --> 02:13.396
And stepped on quite a few toes.

02:13.398 --> 02:14.947
I can live
with some hurt feelings

02:14.949 --> 02:16.816
if we've prevented
more serious harm.

02:16.818 --> 02:18.484
That's not what the guy
in this job

02:18.486 --> 02:21.037
loses sleep over,
or he wouldn't be in it.

02:21.039 --> 02:22.655
What do you lose sleep over?

02:23.624 --> 02:25.875
What I can't see coming.

02:25.877 --> 02:30.046
And hoping that I make
the right moves when it does.

02:30.998 --> 02:32.915
Well, that's a heavy load

02:32.917 --> 02:34.584
to bring to bed
with you every night.

02:34.586 --> 02:36.335
I have a firm mattress.

02:36.337 --> 02:38.588
Let me voice
another point of view.

02:38.590 --> 02:41.974
Quote: "Frank Reagan
is a beat cop

02:41.976 --> 02:44.060
"sitting in a CEO's chair.

02:44.062 --> 02:46.896
"He brings the mentality
of a bullheaded union boss

02:46.898 --> 02:49.265
"to a position that requires
high levels of managerial

02:49.267 --> 02:50.800
"and diplomatic skills.

02:50.802 --> 02:51.968
"His range of vision

02:51.970 --> 02:54.303
"is limited to the interests
of his rank and file,

02:54.305 --> 02:56.739
"to the detriment of his
department's stature

02:56.741 --> 02:58.741
in the community
it's supposed to serve."

02:58.743 --> 03:00.276
Unquote.

03:00.278 --> 03:01.661
Quote-unquote who?

03:01.663 --> 03:04.197
Someone who was
passed over for the job?

03:04.199 --> 03:08.201
No, a high-ranking member
of your own staff.

03:09.620 --> 03:11.454
(sighs)

03:11.456 --> 03:12.672
Is there

03:12.674 --> 03:15.041
a question in there?

03:16.493 --> 03:19.095
(groaning)

03:19.097 --> 03:20.430
(sighs)

03:20.432 --> 03:21.964
All right, here we go.

03:21.966 --> 03:23.099
I'm sorry, Danny.

03:23.101 --> 03:24.834
I don't know why I did that.
You did it

03:24.836 --> 03:26.969
because he was being an ass,
just like anybody else would've.

03:26.971 --> 03:27.882
How is he?

03:27.907 --> 03:29.106
He's got a broken nose
and a concussion.

03:29.107 --> 03:30.339
He's on the way

03:30.341 --> 03:32.191
to the hospital.
Is he gonna be okay?

03:32.193 --> 03:33.943
Hey, we need to talk.

03:33.945 --> 03:36.011
Hang back, all right?

03:36.013 --> 03:38.364
I don't know what's going
on with my buddy Ken,

03:38.366 --> 03:39.565
but we got a problem.

03:39.567 --> 03:40.700
What? What kind of problem?

03:40.702 --> 03:42.184
He wants to press charges.

03:42.186 --> 03:43.185
Whoa, what do you mean?

03:43.187 --> 03:44.487
What are you talking about,
press charges?

03:44.489 --> 03:45.655
He started
the whole thing, kid.

03:45.657 --> 03:46.956
He's a lawyer.
He knows the drill.

03:46.958 --> 03:48.074
Technically, Bobby
assaulted him.

03:48.076 --> 03:49.242
He wants him arrested.

03:49.244 --> 03:51.461
Well, you know what,
I suggest you climb on the bus

03:51.463 --> 03:53.045
with him and talk
some sense into him.

03:53.047 --> 03:54.797
I already tried.
He's insisting.

03:54.799 --> 03:57.800
You know, kid, none of your
lawyer friends next time, okay?

03:57.802 --> 03:58.968
Co and firemen only.

03:58.970 --> 04:00.035
Everything okay?

04:00.037 --> 04:02.171
No, Bobby,
everything's not okay.

04:02.173 --> 04:03.556
What is it?

04:03.558 --> 04:04.874
You're under arrest.

04:04.876 --> 04:06.225
What?

04:06.227 --> 04:07.844
You heard me.

