04:16.720 --> 04:18.504
I love teacher
conference days.

04:18.505 --> 04:20.906
It's like a snow day
without the shoveling.

04:20.909 --> 04:23.159
What time is Dad
coming to get me?

04:23.161 --> 04:26.028
He said 10:00, so I'd plan
on being ready at noon.

04:26.030 --> 04:28.698
Mom, he's busy. That's why
he's always running late.

04:28.700 --> 04:31.066
Take a look at this.

04:31.068 --> 04:32.201
What, your schedule?

04:32.203 --> 04:33.953
Yeah.
Riveting.

04:33.955 --> 04:36.539
The point being,
I'm busy, too, Nicky.

04:36.541 --> 04:38.124
MAN:
Excuse me.

04:38.126 --> 04:39.375
I hope I'm not interrupting.

04:39.377 --> 04:40.793
Uh...

04:40.795 --> 04:43.012
Your assistant said
I should wait here.

04:43.014 --> 04:44.180
Rebekah?

04:44.182 --> 04:46.883
I think she went
to the ladies' room.

04:46.885 --> 04:47.967
Okay.

04:47.969 --> 04:50.303
Um... and you are?

04:50.305 --> 04:51.971
Nathan Anderson.

04:51.973 --> 04:53.272
He's your 9:00.

04:53.274 --> 04:55.975
You must not remember.

04:55.977 --> 04:57.610
I won an auction item
that you offered

04:57.612 --> 04:59.312
over at
the Winter Garden

04:59.314 --> 05:00.930
Charity fund-raiser.

05:00.932 --> 05:02.598
It's a front-row seat

05:02.600 --> 05:03.950
to the criminal justice system.

05:03.952 --> 05:06.118
Right, yes,
of course.

05:06.120 --> 05:07.787
Well, you must
really want to see

05:07.789 --> 05:09.822
how the criminal justice
system works.

05:09.824 --> 05:11.941
Not really, no.

05:11.943 --> 05:13.876
I don't understand.

05:13.878 --> 05:17.446
The truth is, all I want
is a minute of your time.

05:17.448 --> 05:20.800
What's really
going on, Mr. Anderson?

05:22.669 --> 05:25.087
I know who killed my daughter,

05:25.089 --> 05:29.141
and I want you
to put him in jail.

